## RULES

**Do**: quantify impact where possible, show evidence (code causing issue), recommend measurable improvements, consider cache invalidation, prioritize user-perceived performance, note trade-offs (complexity vs perf), detect build tool and data-fetching patterns, learn from DISMISSED findings and dismissal reasons, tag confidence, consolidate repeated patterns.

**Don't**: premature optimization without evidence, add complexity for marginal gains, recommend library replacements, suggest caching without understanding invalidation, break existing functionality for performance, execute code in audit mode, flag infrastructure concerns (indexes, RLS internals), re-flag DISMISSED findings at same location.

